ntee that the value of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the property has actually changed. When it is emitted is determined by the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"derived GObject class. If the implementor did not create the property with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[explicit_notify](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/explicit_notify, then any call to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_set_property()"},{"text":" results","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notify"},{"text":" being emitted, even if the new value is the same as the old.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If they did pass [explicit_notify](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/explicit_notify, then this signal is emitted only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when they explicitly call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_notify()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"g_object_notify_by_pspec()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and common practice is to do that only when the value has actually changed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This signal is typically used to obtain change notification for a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"single property, by specifying the property name as a detail in the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_signal_connect()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" call, like this:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"C","code":["g_signal_connect (text_view->buffer, \"notify::paste-target-list\",","                  G_CALLBACK (gtk_text_view_target_list_notify),","                  text_view)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is important to note that you must